column12: Integrated compressor supporting quick replacement of motor
column13: The utility model discloses an integrated compressor supporting quick replacement of a motor, which relates to the field of compressors and comprises a support plate and a protective cover, the protective cover is fixedly mounted on the top side of the support plate, a gear box and the motor are arranged on the support plate, a motor shaft is fixedly mounted at the output end of the motor, and a connecting shaft is fixedly mounted on the motor. A limiting connecting structure is movably installed on the motor, an L-shaped plate is movably installed on the top side of the supporting plate, and the motor is fixedly installed on the L-shaped plate. According to the utility model, through the arrangement of the L-shaped plate, the insertion plate, the limiting lantern ring and other structures, when the motor fails and cannot be used, the limitation between the motor and the motor shaft and the connecting shaft on the motor can be relieved only by pulling the limiting lantern ring and then rotating the knob, and the motor can be disassembled by horizontally pushing the L-shaped plate, so that the motor can be conveniently overhauled; and a new motor can be replaced during maintenance, so that the normal use of the compressor is not influenced.

column12: A method for examining abnormal situations of client computers in an enterprise
column13: The present invention is related to a method for examining abnormal situations of client computers in an enterprise, especially to the method that at least one server records a status in a usage of at least one client and compares the status with a predefined status to examine at least one situation happened or not for avoiding leakage of the enterprise information. Hence, all of the enterprise information is restricted therein.

column12: PACKAGE SYSTEM
column13: A package system is provided. The package system comprises a carton having at least a first carton panel including a first tab having a first tab edge defined by internal walls of the first panel, a second carton panel opposing the first panel, and a third carton panel between the first carton panel and the second carton panel, the carton having a carton length that is defined as a first distance parallel to the third carton panel between the first carton panel and the second carton panel; and a drawer configured to slide into and out of an interior of the carton, the drawer having at least a first drawer panel opposing the first carton panel, a second drawer panel opposing the second carton panel, and a third drawer panel opposing the third carton panel, the third drawer panel adjoined between the first drawer panel and the second drawer panel.

Sewage suction filtration device for preventing and controlling water environment pollution
column13: The utility model relates to the technical field of sewage treatment, and discloses a sewage suction filtration device for preventing and controlling water environment pollution, which comprises a shell, a speed reducing motor arranged at the upper end of the shell, a water pump arranged at the upper part of the left side of the shell, a water suction pipe arranged at the lower part of the water pump, and a filter bin arranged inside the shell, and a compression bin is arranged in the filtering bin, the inner top wall of the compression bin is rotationally connected with a shaft rod, a support is arranged on the inner top wall of the filtering bin, and a filtering box is arranged on the upper portion of the support. According to the sewage treatment device, by driving the gear motor, the auger blades rotate while driving sewage to move upwards, meanwhile, dregs in the sewage are compressed and preliminarily filtered, finally, the compressed dregs are discharged through the discharging pipe, and the size of the dregs in the sewage is effectively reduced through compression; then the sewage is filtered step by step through the filtering cotton with different pore diameters, so that the filtering cotton can be fully utilized, and the filtering effect is improved.

column12: High-voltage protection device of coil driving device
column13: A high voltage protection device applied to a coil driving device of a DC fan and motor. The coil driving device is connected to the high voltage protection device that has an activation control unit connected to the coil driving device, a logic operation unit that has two input terminals connected to a protection activation signal source and the activation control unit, a high voltage protection unit connected to an output terminal of the logic operation unit and the driving device. When the voltage of the coil driving device is higher than a predetermined value, the potential of a digital signal output is adjusted high and input to the logic operation unit. By logic operation performed on the input digital signal and another digital signal obtained from a protection signal source, a signal is generated to activate the high-voltage protection device, and the operation voltage of coil driving device can return to normal value.

column12: Engine oil circulating filtering structure of inverter compressor
column13: The utility model discloses an engine oil circulating filtering structure of an inverter compressor, which relates to the field of compressors and comprises the inverter compressor, an oil outlet pipe and an oil inlet pipe are arranged on the inverter compressor, a bottom plate is fixedly mounted on the bottom side of the inverter compressor, and four supporting rods are symmetrically and fixedly mounted on the top side of the bottom plate. The same supporting plate is fixedly installed on the top sides of the four supporting rods, the filtering box is fixedly installed on the top side of the supporting plate, the oil inlet pipe is fixedly installed on one side of the filtering box, and the circulating structure is fixedly installed on one side of the filtering box. According to the variable-frequency compressor, through the arrangement of the filter box, the oil well pump and other structures, engine oil in the variable-frequency compressor can be pumped out by starting the oil well pump, the engine oil flows into the variable-frequency compressor again after being filtered by the filter plate in the filter box, and the engine oil is filtered repeatedly until impurities are removed, so that the engine oil can be filtered without pouring out the engine oil; the engine oil can be repeatedly used, and meanwhile, the cost is reduced.

column12: Screw compressor with dustproof structure
column13: The utility model discloses a screw compressor with a dustproof structure, which relates to the field of compressors and comprises a screw compressor, a vent hole is arranged on the screw compressor, two positioning strips are symmetrically and fixedly mounted on the top side of the screw compressor, and driving structures are fixedly mounted on the two positioning strips. And a dust collection box is fixedly mounted on the top side of the screw compressor. According to the screw compressor, through the arrangement of the positioning strip, the motor, the filter plate and other structures, the filter plate can cover the ventilation hole, dust is prevented from falling into the screw compressor, the dust suction hood can move horizontally under the action of the motor, the suction fan can be started while the dust suction hood moves horizontally, and the dust suction hood is prevented from falling into the screw compressor. The suction fan can suck dust attached to the filter plate into the dust collection box, cleaning of the filter plate is achieved, the filter plate can be repeatedly used, the cleanliness and dustproof effect of the filter plate is guaranteed, and then the service life of the screw compressor is prolonged.

column12: DUAL AIR FLOW REBUILDABLE DRIPPING ATOMIZER WITH AN ADJUSTABLE AIR FLOW SLEEVE FOR AN ELECTRONIC CIGARETTE
column13: A dual air flow rebuildable dripping atomizer for use with electronic cigarettes which uses a sleeve lock that allows the user to adjust and direct the air flow is provided. The adjustable air flow sleeve also allows the sleeve to be locked in place preventing the e-liquid from leaking out. Rotating the adjustable air flow sleeve in a clockwise or counter-clockwise direction allows not only the direction of the air flow to be determined but how much air enters an inner air chamber of the atomizer. As a result, a user can determine, for example, the size of the vapor cloud and the intensity of the flavor. Additionally, the adjustable air flow sleeve may be adjusted to block air holes located on an inner edge surface of the adjustable air flow sleeve preventing the e-liquid from leaking.

column12: Automatic Rise Jack Stand
column13: One jack stand includes a stand assembly having a base and a tubular receiving member extending upwardly therefrom. A latch extends from the tubular member. A support bar having upper and lower ends is telescopically housed in a cavity of the tubular member. First and second sides of the bar each have multiple embedded slots. A third side of the bar has multiple holes with angled surfaces such that positioning the latch in any of the holes restricts the bar from moving upwardly yet allows the bar to move downwardly. An automatic lifting device is at least partially inside the cavity and imparts an upward force upon the bar. A stopper selectively interacts with the stand assembly and the bar to restrict the bar from moving downwardly, yet allows the bar to move upwardly. The stopper passes at least partially inside two of the slots to interact with the bar.

column12: Solid garbage collecting device for water environment pollution prevention and control
column13: The utility model relates to the technical field of water environment pollution prevention and control, and discloses a solid garbage collection device for water environment pollution prevention and control, which comprises a barrel body and a filter barrel, the filter barrel is arranged in the barrel body, the bottom of the barrel body is fixedly connected with a pump, the outside of the barrel body is fixedly connected with a hollow ring pipe, and the hollow ring pipe is fixedly connected with the filter barrel. A water outlet of the pump communicates with the hollow annular pipe through a water supply pipe, and four three-way electromagnetic valves are evenly arranged on the periphery of the outer ring of the hollow annular pipe. According to the device, when the three-way electromagnetic valve in any direction is controlled to be completely closed, the device can move towards the direction under the diversion action of the other three three-way electromagnetic valves, solid waste at different positions can be conveniently collected, and in addition, when water does not flow out of the water outlet pipe in the same direction by controlling the three-way electromagnetic valves, the device is convenient to use. According to the device, the effect of in-situ rotation can be achieved, when the device moves to a target area, the action is more accurate, use is convenient and fast, and the applicability is higher.

column12: Multi-leg stand
column13: A multi-leg stand mainly includes a vertical main tube and a tripod structure connected to a lower end of the main tube. The tripod structure includes an inner tube around which a locking element and three unions are sequentially mounted from top to bottom. Three legs are separately connected at inner ends to the three unions. When the locking element engages with the first union at a first locking position, the three legs are folded to locate at the same side of the main tube, and when the locking element engages with the first union at a second locking position, the three legs are equally angularly spaced and radially extended. And, when the locking element is in a releasing position on the inner tube, the three unions may be freely turned in one direction with only one hand to quickly and accurately move into the folded or the spaced position.

column12: Automatic Switch
column13:
Abstract of the Disclosure

    A switch having a body containing a switching circuit; a set of connector ports electrically coupled to the switching circuit; and a plurality of cables fixedly attached to and extending from the body. Each cable in the plurality of cables electrically couples a respective connector plug to the switching circuit, wherein the switching circuit switches to connect each of the set of connector ports to one of the plurality of cables. The body can include a circuit-protecting layer surrounding the switching circuit, an outer case surrounding the circuit-protecting layer, and an anti-slipping layer coating.

Split structure of oil-gas separation core of compressor
column13: The utility model discloses a split structure of an oil-gas separation core of a compressor, which relates to the field of filtering devices and comprises an upper cover and a lower cover, a sleeving structure is fixedly mounted on the upper cover, a filtering inner core is movably sleeved on the sleeving structure, a positioning sleeve rod is fixedly mounted on the lower cover, and a positioning structure is movably mounted on the inner wall of the positioning sleeve rod. A limiting structure is installed on the lower cover in a sliding mode, the sleeving structure comprises a positioning column, the positioning column is fixedly installed on the upper cover, and a plurality of positioning grooves are formed in the positioning column. According to the utility model, the positioning sleeve rod, the positioning column and other structures are arranged, and the upper cover, the lower cover and the filter inner core adopt a split type design, so that when the filter inner core needs to be replaced, the lower cover can be detached from the positioning column only by pulling the baffle downwards and rotating the lower cover, and then the filter inner core can be taken out from the positioning column; the filter inner core is convenient to replace, and the lower cover and the upper cover can be continuously and repeatedly used, so that the effect of saving cost is achieved.

column12: METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR IMPLEMENTING ADAPTIVE FEATURE DETECTION FOR VSLAM SYSTEMS
column13: A method includes receiving a first image, receiving a motion dataset, determining a motion level, determining an initialization state, and determining a tracking level. In a first condition, the method includes generating a first image pyramid, detecting a plurality of features in the first image pyramid using a first detector threshold, and generating a first set of detected keypoints from the plurality of features. In a second condition, the method includes generating a second image pyramid, detecting the plurality of features in the second image pyramid using a second detector threshold, the second detector threshold being less restrictive than the first detector threshold, and generating a second set of detected keypoints. In a third condition, the method includes detecting the plurality of features in the first image according to the first detector threshold and generating a third set of detected keypoints.
column14: GUANGDONG OPPO MOBILE TELECOMMUNICATIONS CORP LTD

column12: METHOD FOR REDUCING UREA DEPOSITS IN AN AFTERTREATMENT SYSTEM
column13: Various systems and methods are described for controlling a diesel aftertreatment system coupled to an exhaust system of an engine which includes a selective catalytic reduction (SCR) catalyst and a diesel particulate filter (PF). In one example, a threshold amount of urea injected to the SCR catalyst is adjusted based on an amount of soot generated by the engine and the total amount of urea injected to the SCR catalyst is limited by the threshold. For example, when the amount of soot generated by the engine is below a first threshold amount, the threshold amount of urea injection is reduced. When the amount of soot generated by the engine is above a second threshold amount, which is greater than the first threshold amount, the threshold amount of urea injection is increased.

column12: KEYBOARD, VIDEO AND MOUSE (KVM) SWITCH
column13: A cable device including a plurality of cables and connecting ports. The cable device may act as a keyboard, video and mouse (KVM) switch system that facilitates controlling different computers with one set of keyboard, video and mouse. In one embodiment, a cable device includes a switching circuit, a plurality of connector ports electrically coupled to the switching circuit, a first cable fixedly connected to the switching circuit, the first cable comprising at least one first connector plug, and a second cable fixedly connected to the switching circuit, the second cable comprising at least one second connector plug, wherein the switching circuit operably selects which of the first and second cables is in communication with the connector ports.

column12: Humidifier and breathing apparatus
column13: The invention relates to a humidifier and a breathing device, and relates to the technical field of medical instruments. The humidifier comprises the water tank, the water tank comprises the tank body and the upper cover, the air inlet channel and the air outlet channel on the upper cover are specially designed, no matter how the water tank inclines, enough height difference can be kept between the first air inlet and the first air outlet of the air inlet channel, and enough height difference can be kept between the second air inlet and the second air outlet of the air outlet channel. Water in the box body is not prone to flowing out through the air inlet channel and the air outlet channel, water in the water tank is prevented from flowing backwards into the main machine and the air conveying pipe, normal operation of the breathing device is guaranteed, and a user is prevented from inhaling water.

column12: VERFAHREN, UM HARNSTOFFABLAGERUNGEN IN EINEM NACHBEHANDLUNGSSYSTEM ZU REDUZIEREN
column13: Verschiedene Systeme und Verfahren werden beschrieben, um ein Dieselnachbehandlungssystem zu steuern, das mit einer Abgasanlage eines Motors gekoppelt ist, die einen SCR-Katalysator und einen Dieselpartikelfilter (PF) umfasst. Bei einem Beispiel wirdr eingespritzten Harnstoffs basierend auf einer durch den Motor erzeugten Rußmenge angepasst, und die Gesamtmenge des in den SCR-Katalysator eingespritzten Harnstoffs wird durch den Schwellenwert begrenzt. Wenn beispielsweise die durch den Motor erzeugte Rußmenge unter einer ersten Schwellenwertmenge liegt, wird die Schwellenwertmenge der Harnstoffeinspritzung reduziert. Wenn die durch den Motor eenge liegt, die größer ist als die erste Schwellenwertmenge, wird die Schwellenwertmenge der Harnstoffeinspritzung erhöht.

column12: Flatbed scanner with space for storing thin objects
Antislip pad for chargeover switch
column13: An antislip pad is designed for protectively mounting onto an end of a changeover switch that is used to change over computer peripherals to be connected to a main unit of the computer. The pad is made of a material providing good softness. When a changeover switch has two antislip pads mounted onto two ends thereof, a bottom surface of the switch is not in direct contact with a surface on which the switch is positioned, protecting the switch from easily slipping over or dropping from the surface. The antislip pad is provided at upper and lower end surfaces with corresponding recesses and projections, respectively, so that two or more antislip pads could be stacked with the projections of an upper pad fitly engaging with the recesses of a lower pad to prevent the stacked pads from slipping relative to each other.

column12: Rack-mounted controller
column13: A rack-mounted controller includes separated main body and control panel electrically connected to one another via a connecting cable, which serves as a path for sending signals between the main body and the control panel. The control panel and the main body are fixed to a front and a rear end, respectively, of a rack for, for example, computer-related apparatus, so that an operator may conveniently observe and operate pushbuttons on the front side of the control panel and has easy access to sockets provided on the rear side of the main body for convenient connection of the controller to external apparatus via the sockets.

column12: Angle-adjustable sun shade
Energy-saving compressed air dryer
column13: The utility model discloses an energy-saving compressed air dryer which comprises a shell, a refrigerator is installed at the bottom of the inner wall of the shell, a cooling water tank is arranged on the upper surface of the refrigerator, the top of the cooling water tank is communicated with a heat exchange cylinder, and the upper surface of the heat exchange cylinder is communicated with an upper water inlet pipe. A water pump is installed in the upper water inlet pipe, one end of the upper water inlet pipe is communicated with a heating water tank, the lower surface of the heating water tank is communicated with a lower water inlet pipe, and one end of the lower water inlet pipe is communicated with the cooling water tank. In the heat exchange cylinder, the gas temperature can be reduced, the water temperature can be increased, water enters the heating water tank after heat exchange, and gas in an exhaust pipe in the heating water tank is dry cooling gas, so that the gas absorbs heat, the effects of water heat dissipation and gas temperature rise are achieved, extra energy does not need to be consumed, the heat absorbed by the water is also recycled, the energy utilization rate is increased, and the energy consumption is reduced. And energy and production cost can be saved.

column12: Rotary supporting base for a display device
column13: In a rotary supporting base, a stationary lower base member has a top surface formed with a ring-supporting region that is confined by an outer periphery concentric with and surrounding an inner periphery, and is formed with an engaging unit on the inner and outer peripheries. A coupling ring plate is disposed at the ring-supporting region, is rotatable relative to the lower base member, and has inner and outer peripheral edges which are in sliding engagement with the engaging unit to retain rotatably the coupling ring plate on the top surface of the lower base member. A rotatable upper base member is disposed on top of the lower base member and is coupled to the coupling ring plate for co-rotation therewith relative to the lower base member. A coupling unit is provided on the coupling ring plate and the upper base member and engages an upright prop of the display device.

column12: Induction diagnostics for skip fire engines
column13: A variety of methods, diagnostic modules and other arrangements for detecting air induction faults during operation of an internal combustion engine are described. In some embodiments, the intake manifold pressure is monitored with the intake pressure being read for each induction opportunity. Induction faults may be detected based at least in part on a comparison of the manifold pressure readings for sequential induction opportunities. In some embodiments, an induction fault is identified when the difference between the manifold pressure associated with an induction opportunity and the immediately preceding induction opportunity exceeds an induction fault threshold.

column12: Gene encoding a putive efflux protein for solvents/antibiotics in Pseudomonas mendocina
column13: This invention relates to the isolation of a novel putative efflux gene from Pseudomonas mendocina . The putative efflux gene is useful for probing an organism's efflux system to gain an understanding of the mechanisms of solvent tolerance. The invention further provides a Pseudomonas mendocina strain deficient in this gene. This strain is unable to grow in the presence of chloramphenicol and, compared to the wildtype strain, grows slowly in the presence of high concentrations of PHBA.

column12: Electronic cigarette outer tube structure based on micropores
column13: The utility model discloses a micropore-based electronic cigarette outer tube structure which comprises a tubular handle, a battery support is arranged in the handle in a penetrating mode, a battery and a circuit board are installed on the battery support, an atomization mechanism is arranged at the end of the handle, and the circuit board and the atomization mechanism are arranged at the two ends of the handle respectively. The handle is in the shape of a three-edged tube, the battery support is arranged in the handle in a penetrating mode, the battery support and the handle are in interference fit, a plurality of micropores with the diameter of 0.3 mm are formed in the handle, the micropores and the circuit board are oppositely arranged, and a gap is formed between the handle and the battery support. Air flow sucked in through the micro holes is conducted to the atomization mechanism through the gaps. According to the utility model, large dust can be prevented from being sucked in, and meanwhile, the attractiveness is better.

column12: Pipe film coating automatic packaging equipment
column13: The invention relates to the technical field of pipe packaging, in particular to pipe film coating automatic packaging equipment. The equipment comprises a rack, a winding packaging mechanism, a shearing mechanism, a heating mechanism, a feeding conveyor and a discharging conveyor. The winding packaging mechanism is arranged on the rack and used for executing the film coating packaging procedure of pipes; the shearing mechanism is arranged on the rack and used for executing the shearing procedure of redundant films after pipe packaging is completed; the heating mechanism is arranged on the rack and is used for executing a heat treatment procedure of the pipes after film coating; the feeding conveyor is arranged at one side of the rack and used for executing the feeding procedure of the pipes; and the discharging conveyor is arranged at the side, away from the feeding conveyor, of the rack and used for executing the discharging procedure of the pipes. The equipment can achieve automatic feeding and discharging, and the problems that in existing manual film sleeving packaging, a film overlying part is looser and prone to falling off, and the working efficiency is low are solved.

column12: Piston air compressor pump head assembling machinery and assembling method
column13: The invention provides piston air compressor pump head assembling machinery and an assembling method. The piston air compressor pump head assembling machinery comprises a mounting bottom plate, supporting legs, supporting rods, a supporting disc, a positioning mechanism, clamping mechanisms and partition plates. By means of the piston air compressor pump head assembling machinery and the assembling method, the problems that piston air compressor pump head assembling operations are difficult to adapt to the radian change of the outer wall of a pump head base seat, and multi-station stable clamping operations can not be provided for the pump head base seat, the possibility that the pump head base seat shakes and deflects due to mechanical vibration is increased, the heights of the two ends of a pump head shell are also difficult to keep consistent while the pump head shell is stably clamped, mounting hole positions between the pump head base seat and the pump head shell are difficult to be quickly and accurately aligned and mounted, batch continuous operations are difficult to perform, and the operation difficulty of the positioning operations of the mounting hole positions is increased can be solved.

column12: Electronic cigarette outer tube structure based on micro hole
column13: The invention discloses an electronic cigarette outer tube structure based on micro holes. The structure comprises a tubular handle, a battery support is arranged in the handle in a penetrating mode,a battery and a circuit board are installed on the battery support, an atomization mechanism is arranged at the end of the handle, the circuit board and the atomization mechanism are arranged at the two ends of the handle respectively, the handle is in a triangular tube shape, the battery support is arranged in the handle in a penetrating mode and is in interference fit with the handle, a plurality of micro holes with the diameter of 0.3 mm are formed in the handle, the micro holes are opposite to the circuit board, gaps are formed between the handle and the battery support, and airflow suckedin through the micro holes is conducted to the atomization mechanism through the gaps. Large dust can be prevented from being sucked in, and meanwhile the attractiveness is better.

column12: LIGHTING APPARATUS
column13: A lighting apparatus includes a lamp seat, a lighting unit, a housing, and an abutment unit. The lamp seat includes a support portion. The lighting unit is disposed on the lamp seat and includes a circuit board disposed on the support portion, and at least one lighting element mounted on the circuit board for emitting light. The housing surrounds and covers the lighting unit, and includes a cover flange connected to the lamp seat. The abutment unit is disposed between the housing and the lighting unit for abutting against and securing the circuit board on the support portion.

column12: Tie strap manufacture method
column13: The present invention provides a tie strap manufacture method, which includes the following steps: blending polymer material, calcium carbon compound and filler; further blending the blended material with an additive as a tie strap composition; sending to an extruder for extrusion, such that the tie strap composition is formed as an elastic structure body, which is then cut into the tie strap product. Thus, the tie strap can be formed by continuously supplying material and is directly cut to form the tie strap product with elasticity. The present invention may reduce the manufacturing cost, increase the production speed, and generate the effects of enhancing using convenience and increasing application variety.

column12: METHOD AND DEVICE FOR PURIFYING AND DESALTING BIOLOGICAL SAMPLE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a sample processing technique for purifying biological and chemical samples.

SOLUTION: This method is particularly suitable for preparing samples for mass spectrometry. The method is carried out using an article having at least one well. The surface of the well is made hydrophobic at least partially and/or denatured using a biospecific ligand. A targeted solvent such as a salt or an impurity of a small molecule is removable from a solution to provide a purified solution composed of a desired kind of solvent such as peptide and proteins.

column12: Hydrophilic Coating Methods for Chemically Inert Substrates
column13: The present invention discloses methods for producing a hydrophilic coating for chemically inert substrates such as fluoropolymers using a multi-step coating process consisting of (1) producing a plasma polymerization coating of alcohol compounds on the substrate, followed by (2) sequentially contacting the plasma polymer coated substrate with one or more solutions of hydrophilic polymers. Advantageously, such methods produce a strongly adhered hydrophilic coating for fluoropolymer and other chemically inert substrates.

column12: Automatic machining equipment and method for casting forming of screw pump rotor
column13: The invention relates to automatic machining equipment and method for casting forming of a screw pump rotor. The automatic machining equipment is provided with a mounting plate arranged on the ground, mounting columns are arranged at the two ends of the mounting plate correspondingly, end clamping devices for clamping the ends of the screw pump rotor are arranged on the opposite sides of the two mounting columns, a motor for driving the end clamping devices to rotate is arranged on the opposite sides of the two mounting columns, supporting columns are arranged on the upper end sides of the two mounting columns and extend upwards, supporting rods are arranged at the upper ends of the opposite sides of the two supporting columns, and grinding devices for grinding the screw pump rotor are arranged on the supporting rods. The screw pump rotor is fixed through the end clamping devices, the screw pump rotor is driven to rotate through the motor, and then the surface of the screw pump rotor is ground through the grinding device, so that the surface of the screw pump rotor is smooth.

column12: Product correcting device of packaging equipment
column13: The invention relates to the field of material conveying, in particular to a product correcting device of packaging equipment. The product correcting device comprises a rack, a conveying belt, a blocking device, a spacing control system, a sorting system, a guide mechanism and a correcting device, wherein the rack is used for fixing all components and parts; the conveying belt is used for conveying products; the blocking device is arranged at the upper position of the rack and used for preventing the products from being blocked; the spacing control system is arranged at the rear end of the blocking device and used for controlling the distance between the products; the sorting system is arranged at the rear end of the spacing control system and used for distinguishing the states of the products and transferring the products to corresponding positions; the guide mechanism is arranged at the rear end of the sorting system and used for further correcting the positions of the products; and the correcting device is arranged above the guide mechanism and used for further correcting the products in the channel of the guide mechanism. According to the scheme, the positions of the products can be corrected, and the effect of accurately packaging the products is achieved.

column12: Multi-gear adjusting and continuous pulling and inserting indicating device for electronic cigarette
column13: The utility model discloses a multi-gear adjusting and continuous plugging indicating device for an electronic cigarette. A connecting contact is used for being electrically contacted with a cigarette cartridge of the electronic cigarette; the voltage regulating circuit is connected between the connecting contact and the main control unit; the light control unit is connected between the LED lamp group and the main control unit; the plugging detection unit is connected to the main control unit, and the plugging detection unit is used for detecting the on-off state of the smoke cartridge and the connection contact and outputting a continuous plugging signal to the main control unit when the smoke cartridge and the connection contact are continuously powered off for three times within a preset time; and the main control unit is used for controlling the voltage regulating circuit to increase the voltage of the connecting contact to a preset value according to the continuous plugging signal, and controlling the LED lamp group to emit a corresponding light signal through the light control unit. The power supply voltage of the smoke cartridge can be flexibly adjusted, so that various smoking requirements are met.

column12: OPTICALLY CLEAR BIOCOMPATIBLE AND DURABLE HYDROPHILIC COATING PROCESS FOR CONTACT LENSES
column13: The present invention discloses methods for producing an optically clear, biocompatible and durable hydrophilic coating for contact lenses comprising the steps of first applying a polymer coating on the contact lenses by plasma polymerization of monomers containing ethylene glycol groups, followed by incubating the coated contact lenses at an elevated temperature to remove the volatile residual monomers trapped inside the coating. Advantageously, such methods produce an optically clear, biocompatible and durable hydrophilic surface for contact lenses in a dry, solvent-free process.

METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR PURIFYING AND DESALTING BIOLOGICAL SAMPLES
column13: The subject invention provides a sample processing technique for purifying a biological or chemical sample. The invention is particularly well-suited to prepare a sample for mass spectrometry. The process is to be performed in an article having at least one well, in which the surface of the well is at least partially hydrophobic and/or modified with bio-specific ligands. Targeted solutes, such as salts or small molecule contaminants, can be removed from a solution to allow for a purified solution of a desired type of solute, such as peptides and/or proteins.

column12: Oil leakage prevention mechanism of electronic cigarette
column13: The utility model discloses an electronic cigarette oil leakage prevention mechanism, the electronic cigarette comprises a handle and a cigarette cartridge, the lower end of the cigarette cartridge is provided with an atomization support, an atomizer is inserted in the atomization support, the lower end of the atomization support is provided with a guide groove, the guide groove extends towards the outer side of the atomizer, and the atomizer is inserted into the guide groove. A guide groove is formed in the upper end of the atomization support and communicated with an air inlet hole of the atomizer, an end cover is fixed to the lower end of the atomization support and covers the guide groove, a through hole is formed in the end cover and communicated with the guide groove, and the through hole and the air inlet hole are arranged in a staggered mode. According to the electronic cigarette, tobacco tar can be effectively prevented from leaking to the outer side of the through hole, the overall performance of the electronic cigarette is greatly improved, and user requirements and market requirements are well met.

column12: Methods for covalently attaching molecules on surfaces and producing non-fouling surfaces
column13: The present invention relates to methods of modifying the chemical structure of a surface by covalently attaching molecules containing desired functional groups on the surface using plasma energy. In these methods, chemical compounds containing the desired functional groups and having a vapor pressure lower than 0.001 bar are exposed in the plasma chamber together with the substrate. Surface area of the chemical compound is optimized to generate adequate evaporation rate. The modification of the substrate surface is achieved in a plasma state generated from the vapor of the chemical compounds; while the evaporation of the chemical compounds is accelerated by the plasma energy. Methods for producing non-fouling surface by covalently attaching ethylene glycol oligomers on the surface are disclosed.

column12: Battery bracket mounting structure and mounting process of electronic cigarette
column13: The invention discloses a battery bracket mounting structure of an electronic cigarette. The structure comprises a tubular handle, a battery bracket is arranged in the handle in a penetrating manner,a battery accommodating opening is formed in the side part of the battery bracket, a battery is arranged in the battery accommodating opening, and the battery is bonded and fixed with the inner wall of the battery accommodating opening through glue. column13: The utility model belongs to the technical field of tool machining, and particularly relates to a double-end stud for a tool and a modular tool. The double-end stud for the cutter comprises a stud body; and the positioning part is positioned on the stud body and is used for isolating the thread to form two thread sections, so that the screwing depth of the corresponding thread section is positioned when one thread section is connected with the inner screw hole of the tool bit or the other thread section is connected with the inner screw hole of the tool handle. According to the double-end stud for the cutter, the positioning part is arranged on the stud body, so that the screwing-in depth of the corresponding threaded section is positioned when one threaded section is connected with the inner threaded hole of the cutter head or the other threaded section is connected with the inner threaded hole of the cutter handle, and the problem of threaded connection strength caused by improper use is solved; and after the double-end stud for the tool is used in the modular tool, the tool can be replaced by replacing the tool bit, the tool handle is reserved, and the overall use cost of the tool is reduced.

column12: SIDE-EMISSION TYPE LIGHTING DEVICE
column13: A side-emission type lighting device includes a lamp seat, and a lighting unit disposed on the lamp seat. The lighting unit includes a mounting face that is perpendicular to a lamp axis, and at least one lighting element mounted on the mounting face for radiating emitted light away from the mounting face. The lighting device also includes a light-transmissive housing that surrounds and covers the lighting unit, that is disposed on the lamp seat, and that includes an end wall and a peripheral wall. The end wall is disposed distal to the lamp seat, and the peripheral wall extends from a periphery of the end wall towards the lamp seat. The lighting device also includes a light guide disposed between the light-transmissive housing and the lighting unit. The light guide includes a redirecting face that receives and redirects emitted light from the lighting element.

Self-floating drilling tool leakage point position detection device
column13: The invention discloses a self-floating drilling tool leakage point position detection device. The self-floating drilling tool leakage point position detection device comprises an upper pressure measurement pup joint, a lower pressure measurement pup joint and a self-floating pup joint, the self-floating pup joint is a hollow circular pipe, and the upper end and the lower end of the self-floatingpup joint are correspondingly connected with the upper pressure measurement pup joint and the lower pressure measurement pup joint through threads. The upward buoyancy of the self-floating pup joint under the well is larger than the sum of the weight of the upper pressure measuring pup joint, the weight of the lower pressure measuring pup joint and the self-weight of the self-floating pup joint. The pup joints can detect the position of a piercing leakage point of a drilling tool, and the leakage point searching accuracy and efficiency are improved.

A connecting contact is used for being electrically contacted with a cigarette cartridge of the electronic cigarette; a voltage regulating circuit is connected between the connecting contact and a main control unit; a light control unit is connected between the LED lamp set and themain control unit; a plugging detection unit is connected to the main control unit, and is used for detecting the on-off state of the smoke cartridge and the connecting contact, and outputting a continuous plugging signal to the main control unit when the smoke cartridge and the connecting contact are continuously powered off for three times within a preset time; and the main control unit is usedfor controlling the voltage regulating circuit to increase the voltage of the connecting contact to a preset value according to the continuous plugging signal, and controlling the LED lamp group to emit a corresponding optical signal through the light control unit. The power supply voltage of the smoke cartridge can be flexibly adjusted, and then various smoking requirements are met.

column12: CABLE ORGANIZER STRUCTURE
column13: A cable organizer unit includes a foam structure main body. The foam structure main body has a base section, a first extension end and a second extension end. The first and second extension ends respectively extend from two sides of the base section toward the middle of the base section. Each of the first and second extension ends having a free end. The free ends of the first and second extension ends are adjacent to each other. The first and second extension ends and the base section together define a receiving space. By means of the cable organizer unit, the cable can be easily and quickly fixed.

column12: Covalently Attached Antioxidant Coatings
column13: The present invention discloses methods for producing a covalently attached antioxidant coating using a multi-step coating process consisting of (1) exposing the substrate surface to plasma polymerization to produce a surface containing functional groups; (2) contacting the surface containing functional groups with crosslinking agents to produce a reactive surface; (3) contacting the reactive surface with a solution of one or more antioxidant compounds or a solution of one or more antioxidant-containing polymers. Alternatively, the third step is replaced by (3) contacting the reactive surface with a solution of one or more polymers to produce a polymer coated surface and (4) covalently attaching one or more antioxidant compounds to the polymer coated surface.

column12: CROSS-LINKED PEG POLYMER COATING FOR IMPROVING BIOCOMPATIBILITY OF MEDICAL DEVICES
column13: The present invention relates to a cross-linked PEG polymer coating that is hydrophilic, lubricious, and resistant to adsorption of biological matters including proteins and cells. The coating is created using plasma glow discharge polymerization of organic compounds with a formula R(OCH2CH2)nOH, where R is an alkane group with 1 - 4 carbon atoms and n = 1 - 6.

column12: Electronic cigarette with hanging rope
column13: The utility model discloses an electronic cigarette with a hanging rope, which comprises a handle, a smoke cartridge and the hanging rope, the smoke cartridge is matched with the handle in an inserting way, the hanging rope comprises a rope body, a lantern ring made of a soft rubber material is formed at the end part of the rope body, the lantern ring is sleeved on the handle, and the lantern ring and the handle are tightly matched. According to the electronic cigarette, the hanging rope is configured for the electronic cigarette, the lantern ring is arranged at the end of the rope body of the hanging rope, and the lantern ring is made of elastic soft rubber materials, so that the lantern ring can be tightly connected to the handle in a sleeving mode, and under the combined action of the rope body, the lantern ring and the handle, a user can conveniently hold and carry the electronic cigarette, and the electronic cigarette is convenient to use. Moreover, the electronic cigarette can be effectively prevented from sliding off, and the user requirement and the market requirement are well met.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR PURIFYING AND DESALTING BIOLOGICAL SAMPLES
column13: The subject invention provides a sample processing technique for purifying a biological or chemical sample. The invention is particularly well-suited to prepare a sample for mass spectrometry. The process is to be performed in an article having at least one well, in which the surface of the well is at least partially hydrophobic and/or modified with bio-specific ligands. Targeted solutes, such as salts or small molecule contaminants, can be removed from a solution to allow for a purified solution of a desired type of solute, such as peptides and/or proteins.

column12: Continuous working type packaging paper conveying device
column13: The invention relates to a continuous working type packaging paper conveying device which comprises a bottom plate, side plates, packaging paper, a rotating device, guide mechanisms, early warning devices, packaging paper replacing devices and binding devices, wherein the side plate is fixedly mounted above the bottom plate; the packaging paper is axially placed on the two sides of the side plates; the rotating device is axially arranged on the side plates on the two sides, and the rotating device is used for driving packaging paper to be conveyed; the guide mechanisms are arranged in the side plates, and the guide mechanisms are used for guiding conveying of the packaging paper; the early warning devices are arranged on the side plates, and the early warning devices play a role in early warning when the packaging paper is about to be used up; the packaging paper replacing devices are horizontally arranged on the two sides of the side plates, and the packaging paper replacing devices are used for rapidly replacing the packaging paper; and the binding devices are arranged on the side plates, and the binding devices are used for binding packaging paper joints. According to the scheme, the technical purpose of continuous working type conveying of the packaging paper is achieved.

column12: Smoke cartridge with conical air passage

And the wide opening extends to the end part of the cartridge shell. The electronic cigarette can prevent tobacco tar from being sucked into the oral cavity along with smoke, the situation that the mouth is scalded can be avoided, and then the use experience is improved.

High-efficiency rapid article packaging device
column13: The invention relates to the field of automatic packaging, and particularly relates to a high-efficiency rapid article packaging device. The high-efficiency rapid article packaging device comprises a rack, a feeding device, a conveying device, a filling device, a first correcting device, a material moving device and a discharging device; the feeding device is fixedly installed at one end of the rack and horizontally arranged in the long edge direction of the rack; the conveying device is fixedly installed on the rack and fixedly installed in the rack; the filling device is vertically arranged beside the rack, and the output end of the filling device faces the top end of the conveying device; the first correcting device is fixedly installed on the rack and fixedly installed beside the rack, and the output end of the first correcting device faces the interior of the rack; the material moving device is fixedly installed at one end of the rack and arranged away from the feeding device; and the discharging device is arranged beside the material moving device, and the end of the discharging device is connected with the material moving device in an abutting manner. The device can automatically complete automatic feeding, filling and discharging work of packaging boxes, time and labor are saved, and the work efficiency is improved.

column12: Gene encoding a putative efflux protein for solvents/antibiotics in pseudomonas mendocina
column13: This invention relates to the isolation of a novel putative efflux gene from Pseudomonas mendocina. The putative efflux gene is useful for probing an organism's efflux system to gain an understanding of the mechanisms of solvent tolerance. The invention further provides a Pseudomonas mendocina strain deficient in this gene. This strain is unable to grow in the presence of chloramphenicol and, compared to the wildtype strain, grows slowly in the presence of high concentrations of PHBA.

column12: ELASTIC ZIP TIE
column13: An elastic zip tie is integrally molded from foam rubber, and includes a long strip of strap, a head located at a front end of the strap, and a plurality of flexible grips axially spaced on an upper and a lower surface of the strap. At least one holding space is defined by between any two adjacent axially-spaced flexible grips. The head has a thickness defined between two lateral sides thereof and is substantially larger than a longitudinal length of the holding space, i.e., a distance between two adjacent flexible grips. When a tail end of the strap is extended through the head for the latter to rest on the strap in a selected holding space, the flexible grips located immediately before and behind the holding space are elastically pressed against the two opposite lateral sides of the head to thereby firmly hold the latter in the holding space.

column12: Battery bracket mounting structure of electronic cigarette
column13: The utility model discloses a battery bracket mounting structure of an electronic cigarette, which comprises a tubular handle, a battery bracket is arranged in the handle in a penetrating manner, a battery accommodating opening is formed in the side part of the battery bracket, a battery is arranged in the battery accommodating opening, and the battery is adhered and fixed with the inner wall of the battery accommodating opening through glue. During assembly, the battery is firstly installed in the battery containing opening, then the battery and the inner wall of the battery containing opening are bonded and fixed through glue, finally, the battery support penetrates into the handle, and the battery support is tightly matched with the handle, so that the battery support can be firmly fixed on the basis of the fixing mode. The stability and the reliability of battery installation are greatly improved, the situations of battery loosening and the like in the using process can be avoided, and the application requirements are well met.

column12: CABLE ORGANIZATION UNIT
column13: A cable organization unit includes a foam structure body. The foam structure body has a base section. The base section has a first face. A first extension end perpendicularly protrudes from a middle section of the first face of the base section. A second extension end and a third extension end respectively extend from two sides of the base section to the first extension end. Each of the first, second and third extension ends has a free end. The free ends of the first, second and third extension ends are adjacent to each other, whereby the first, second and third extension ends define a first receiving space and a second receiving space. By means of the cable organization unit, a user can much more conveniently organize cables.

column12: Tinplate-based cigarette cartridge and cigarette rod mounting mechanism
column13: The utility model discloses a tinplate-based cigarette cartridge and cigarette rod mounting mechanism, which comprises a cigarette rod, a cigarette cartridge and a tinplate sleeve, a socket for inserting the cigarette cartridge is formed at the top end of the cigarette rod, a magnet and a metal probe are arranged at the bottom of the socket, two metal contacts are arranged on the lower end face of the cigarette cartridge, and the metal contacts correspond to the metal probe one by one. The tinplate sleeve is arranged at the lower end of the smoke cartridge in a sleeving mode, an avoiding opening is formed in the tinplate sleeve, the metal contact piece is located in the avoiding opening, and when the lower end of the smoke cartridge is inserted into the inserting opening, the magnet and the tinplate sleeve are magnetically attracted, and meanwhile the metal contact piece and the metal probe are tightly connected in an abutting mode. According to the electronic cigarette, magnets do not need to be arranged for the cigarette cartridge and the cigarette rod respectively, so that a group of magnets can be saved, meanwhile, the magnetic attraction matching between the tinplate sleeve and the magnets is not limited by the direction of a magnetic field, the electronic cigarette is easier to produce and convenient to assemble, and the production efficiency and the product yield are greatly improved.

column12: METHOD FOR MAKING ELECTRICAL CONNECTIONS BETWEEN CONDUCTORS SEPARATED BY A DIELECTRIC
column13: A method for making electrical connections between conductive contact pads separated by a dielectric separation layer (12) is disclosed. In the method of the present invention, a structural separation layer is provided that separates at least two aligned conductive contact pads (14a, 14b). The electrical connection between the contact pads (14a, 14b) is made by using a tool (20) to apply pressure, heat, mechanical vibration, or a combination thereof to one of the contact pads (14a). In this manner, a contact pad is deformed and pressed through the separation layer (12), thereby displacing the separation layer material between the contact pads (14a, 14b). In this manner, no prefabricated hole is required in the separation layer (12).

column12: DURABLE HYDROPHILIC COATING PRODUCED BY MULTIPLE STAGE PLASMA POLYMERIZATION
column13: The present invention discloses methods for producing a durable hydrophilic coating for hydrophobic substrates such as silicone elastomer using multiple stage plasma polymerization of compounds containing hydrophilic functional groups. The first stage plasma polymerization creates a highly cross-linked hydrophilic polymer barrier to prevent hydrophobic moieties from migrating from the bulk to the surface; the final stage creates a hydrogel-like layer on the top of the coating to render the surface more hydrophilic and lubricious. Advantageously, such methods produce a durable hydrophilic surface that resists hydrophobic recovery of highly hydrophobic substrates such as silicone elastomer.

The elastic main body has an anchor section and an insertion section outward extending from the anchor section. The first raised section is formed on one side of the insertion section and projects from the side of the insertion section. column12: Electronic cigarette state monitoring and protecting mechanism
column13: The utility model discloses an electronic cigarette state monitoring and protecting mechanism which comprises a handle, an inner support is arranged in the handle, a battery, a PCB (printed circuit board), a connecting contact and a smoking frequency detection unit are arranged on the inner support, a voltage regulating circuit and a main control unit are arranged on the PCB, and the connecting contact is used for electrically contacting with a cigarette cartridge of an electronic cigarette; the voltage regulating circuit is connected between the connecting contact and the main control unit; the smoking frequency detection unit is connected to the main control unit, and the smoking frequency detection unit is used for detecting the air exhaust state of the smoke cartridge and outputting a smoking signal to the main control unit when the smoking frequency detection unit detects that the smoke cartridge exhausts air; and the main control unit is used for counting the smoking signal output by the smoking frequency detection unit, controlling the connection contact to be powered off through the voltage regulating circuit when the counting value reaches a set value, and controlling the voltage regulating circuit to load the voltage signal to the connection contact until the smoke cartridge is connected with the connection contact again. According to the utility model, the working state of the electronic cigarette can be monitored in real time and protected in time.

column12: TIE MANUFACTURING METHOD
column13: A tie manufacturing method includes steps of: mixing materials of polymer material, calcium carbon compound and filling; further mixing the mixture of the materials and an additive with each other as compositions of the tie and feeding the mixture of the compositions of the tie into an extruder for extruding the mixture; forming an elastic structure body from the extruded compositions of the tie; and cutting the elastic structure body to form the tie products. The materials of the ties can be uninterruptedly supplied and formed and directly cut into elastic tie products. Accordingly, the manufacturing cost is lowered and the production rate is increased. Moreover, the tie can be more conveniently and diversely used.

column12: Methods for Covalently Attaching Molecules on Surfaces and Producing Non-fouling Surfaces
column13: The present invention relates to methods of modifying the chemical structure of a surface by covalently attaching molecules containing desired functional groups on the surface using plasma energy. In these methods, chemical compounds containing the desired functional groups and having a vapor pressure lower than 0.001 bar are exposed in the plasma chamber together with the substrate. Surface area of the chemical compound is optimized to generate adequate evaporation rate. The modification of the substrate surface is achieved in a plasma state generated from the vapor of the chemical compounds; while the evaporation of the chemical compounds is accelerated by the plasma energy. Methods for producing non-fouling surface by covalently attaching ethylene glycol oligomers on the surface are disclosed.

Automatic packaging equipment adjusting mechanism based on intelligent manufacturing
column13: The invention relates to the technical field of automatic mechanical packaging, in particular to an automatic packaging equipment adjusting mechanism based on intelligent manufacturing. The automatic packaging equipment adjusting mechanism comprises a base and a posture adjusting device, and the posture adjusting device is used for placing an object to be packaged. The automatic packaging equipment adjusting mechanism is characterized in that the posture adjusting device comprises a horizontal adjusting device and a rotary adjusting device, the horizontal adjusting device is used for adjusting the position of the object placed on the horizontal adjusting device, and the horizontal adjusting device comprises a square plate, a first adjusting mechanism and a second adjusting mechanism, wherein the first adjusting mechanism and the second adjusting mechanism are arranged on the square plate. The rotary adjusting device is used for adjusting the orientation direction of the feeding end and the discharging end of the horizontal adjusting device, and the horizontal adjusting device is fixedly arranged at the working end of the rotary adjusting device. The automatic packaging equipment adjusting mechanism can quickly and accurately complete object position adjusting work of the automatic packaging equipment, so that the object packaged every time can be located at a correct and standard position, and the product packaging quality and the packaging work efficiency of the equipment are improved.

An RF transmitter using class E amplifiers
column13: An RF modulator and amplifier comprises an improved envelope elimination and restoration (EER) arrangement wherein an auxiliary class E amplifier 14 fed by a small fixed bias voltage Vb provides a signal for cancelling unwanted carrier feedthrough from the input to the output of the main class E amplifier 10. This removes an amplitude offset in the output waveform. The required path phase difference for cancellation may be ensured by use of couplers 12,16 with phase differences between ports or by use of a phase shifter (figure 3). Carrier feedthrough in class E amplifiers is a problem because the drive waveform must be of large amplitude to ensure good switching performance of the transistor.

column12: Collapsible frame of a bicycle and locking device for the same
Collapsible frame of a bicycle and locking device for the same
column13: A collapsible frame of a bicycle includes a tube and a locking device. The tube is collapsible and includes a first section, a second section and a pivoting joint. The pivoting joint connects the first section with the second section. The locking device is mounted on the tube at a position adjacent to the pivoting joint, and includes a body, a movable locking member, a resilient member and a stationary locking member. The body is pivotally mounted on the first section. The movable locking member is movably mounted on the body and includes a hook. The resilient member is mounted between the body and the movable locking member to provide a resilient force to the movable locking member. The stationary locking member is mounted on the second section on which the hook is engaged to lock the locking device. The locking device ensures that the first section and the second section will never depart from each other during biking.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR MANAGING APPLICATION INSTALLATION FOR MOBILE DEVICE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a system and a method for managing application installation for a mobile device.

SOLUTION: This method and the system are provided for installing the applications (10A, 10A' and 10A") in a plurality of mobile devices from a storage source (4, 4A and 4B), and include a step of storing a plurality of applications on the storage sources (4, 4A and 4B) when each mobile device (3) is a different kind. Each application (10A, 10A' and 10A") is designed for a unique type of mobile device. The mobile device (3) is connected to the storage source (4, 4A and 4B), and the type of mobile device is detected. The selected application (10A, 10A' and 10A") is then transferred to the mobile device.

column12: Gesture and touch-based interactivity with objects using 3D zones in an interactive system
column13: An interactive, zone-based installation enables a user to interact with an object, such as a retail product, an appliance, a food item, a poster, a non-touch screen monitor, an object of nature, or any other of a number of various items. A user approaches the object and reaches for it. The installation displaying the object has a sensor such as a camera. The sensor is coupled to a processor and continuously feeding an image depth buffer stream. Within the field of view of the sensor is a 3D zone. The zone is strategically positioned near or around the object. When a user reaches for the object there is a change in the depth buffer data stream. If this change exceeds time and sensitivity thresholds implying an intentional gesture by the user, an output event is triggered by the processor.

column12: Analytical Instrument with Collimated and Adjustable Length Optical Path
column13: This disclosure relates generally to analytical instruments for measuring one or more properties of specimens or samples to be analyzed and, more particularly, to an analytical instrument with an adjustable optical path length. An analytical instrument may include a specimen support upon which a specimen may rest and a compression plate for controllably adjusting an optical path length of the specimen between the specimen support and the compression plate. In particular, a specimen may contact both the specimen support and the compression plate such that controlling a distance of the compression plate with respect to the specimen support effectively controls the optical path length of the specimen. An analytical instrument may include collimating lenses to collimate electromagnetic energy for transmission through a specimen and converging lenses for directing electromagnetic energy transmitted through the specimen into one or more sensors.

column12: Respirating gas supply method and apparatus therefor
column13: In various embodiments of a respirating gas supply method and apparatus a control circuit (32) responsive to a sensor (28) operates valve means (26) to supply pulses of respirating gas through a single hose cannula (48) to an in vivo respiratory system when negative pressure indicative of inspiration is sensed by the sensor (28). The control circuit (32) operates the valve (26) to communicate the in vivo respiratory system with a supply of gas (20) only if the negative pressure sensed by the sensor (28) does not occur within a predetermined yet selectively variable required minimum delay interval between successive pulsed applications of gas to the in vivo respiratory system. The pulse of gas applied to the in vivo respiratory system can be spiked pulses or square pulses. Humidifiers, nebulizers and sources of a second gas are provided in accordance with various embodiments. Apnea event detection is also provided.

column12: PREFERENCE LEARNING WITH CLUSTERING
column13: In one aspect, there is provided a method for preference learning. The method may include: determining whether existing data associated with a user is available, wherein the existing data includes preference weights assigned to user clusters; when existing data associated with the user is unavailable: selecting, based on a ranking of the user clusters, a user cluster; providing, based on a selected user cluster, recommendations to the user; and assigning, based on a response of the user to the recommendations, a preference weight to each of the selected user cluster and/or another user cluster; and when existing data associated with the user is available, determining whether to exploit the existing data or to explore new preferences for the user, wherein exploiting comprises providing the recommendations based on the existing data, and wherein exploring comprises providing the recommendations by selecting a user cluster not assigned a preference weight.

PREFERENCE LEARNING WITH CLUSTERING
column13: In one aspect, there is provided a method for preference learning. The method may include: determining whether existing data associated with a user is available, wherein the existing data includes preference weights assigned to user clusters; when existing data associated with the user is unavailable: selecting, based on a ranking of the user clusters, a user cluster; providing, based on a selected user cluster, recommendations to the user; and assigning, based on a response of the user to the recommendations, a preference weight to each of the selected user cluster and/or another user cluster; and when existing data associated with the user is available, determining whether to exploit the existing data or to explore new preferences for the user, wherein exploiting comprises providing the recommendations based on the existing data, and wherein exploring comprises providing the recommendations by selecting a user cluster not assigned a preference weight.

column12: Analytical instrument with collimated and adjustable length optical path
column13: This disclosure relates generally to analytical instruments for measuring one or more properties of specimens or samples to be analyzed and, more particularly, to an analytical instrument with an adjustable optical path length. An analytical instrument may include a specimen support upon which a specimen may rest and a compression plate for controllably adjusting an optical path length of the specimen between the specimen support and the compression plate. In particular, a specimen may contact both the specimen support and the compression plate such that controlling a distance of the compression plate with respect to the specimen support effectively controls the optical path length of the specimen. An analytical instrument may include collimating lenses to collimate electromagnetic energy for transmission through a specimen and converging lenses for directing electromagnetic energy transmitted through the specimen into one or more sensors.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR MANAGING APPLICATION INSTALLATION FOR A MOBILE DEVICE
column13: A method and system of installing applications (10A, l0A', 10A") for a plurality of mobile devices from a storage source (4, 4A, 4B), wherein each mobile device (3) is of a different type, includes storing on the storage source (4, 4A, 4B) a plurality of applications. Each application (10A, 10A', 10") is designed for a unique type of mobile device. The mobile device (3) is connected to the storage source (4, 4A, 4B) and the type of mobile device is detected. A selected application (10A, 10A', 10") is then transferred to the mobile device.

column12: Truck tire pressure detection system
column13: The invention discloses a truck tire pressure detection system, and relates to the technical field of pressure detection, the truck tire pressure detection system comprises a machine shell, a lifting mechanism, a tire replacing mechanism and a working mechanism are arranged in the machine shell, the lifting mechanism can lift the part, needing to be lifted, of the working mechanism and move the part lifted by the working mechanism to the position in front of a defective tire, and the tire replacing mechanism is arranged in the machine shell. The tire replacing mechanism can detect the pressure of a tire and detach the tire with a detached screw to replace the tire with a new tire, and the working mechanism can detach the screw of the defective tire or detect the position of an air valve of the tire and conduct inflation action. By judging the external pressure of the tire, the air valve does not need to be connected through a professional tool, hidden dangers caused by manual detection are reduced, the connecting rod moving blocks at the left end and the right end can synchronously advance, the connecting rods are driven to rotate, and the working plate is lifted, so that the working plate can be hidden underground at ordinary times; the damage is reduced.

column12: Method of processing a searching service for carriage information
column13: PURPOSE: A method for processing a search service of the transportation information is provided to enhance the search efficiency for a proper transportation travel fit to a transportation request condition and to construct an interactive real time processing environment. CONSTITUTION: The search service system includes a server(100), a plurality of customer computer(102) and a plurality of marine transportation businessman's computer(104). The terminals connects to each other through a network such as the Internet, a LAN(Local Area Network) and a WAN(Wide Area Network). The computer of marine transportation businessman provides the transportation line data to the server. The transportation line data received from the marine transportation businessman includes some ship transportation lines and some transportation lines for the ship transportation lines. Each transportation line includes a ship name, a transportation travel number, some ports and an arrival date. The customer searches a proper transportation line to carry the articles by connecting to the server through the computer of customer.

column12: Method of fabricating plastic strips and an extruder structure therefor
column13: In a method of fabricating plastic strips and an extruder structure therefor, a plastic extruder is used to melt plastic or acrylic raw materials and to extrude the same in the form of soft plastic strips, which can be bent by hand to form a shape by following a pattern that is a line or a recess formed in a mold plate. The plastic strip is allowed to cool to form a product with the desired shape.

column12: Cabinet for storing rack mount computer
column13: A cabinet for storing a plurality of rack mount computers is described. The rack mount computers respectively include a plurality of hosts each having a hard disk. The cabinet includes a plurality of drawer-shaped chassis. They are arranged side by side, for respectively contain the hosts. At least one of the rack mount computers can be pulled out by pulling out the drawer-shaped chassis containing the one of the rack mount computers. The pulled drawer-shaped chassis has an L-shaped cap on the hard disk of the host of the pulled rack mount computer.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR MANAGING APPLICATION INSTALLATION FOR A MOBILE DEVICE
column13: A method of installing program applications from a storage source onto a mobile device comprises storing a setup package file on the storage source. A single file has a first portion comprising application specific information and a second portion comprising application files. The application specific information includes setup information. The setup package file is transferred and stored on the mobile device. The setup package file stored o n the mobile device is unpacked to create an executable application program on the mobile device . The step of unpacking includes dynamically truncating the setup package file by relocati ng an end-of-file marker of the setup package file during unpacking.

column12: ANTI-MISINSERTION STRUCTURE OF SOCKET CONNECTOR
column13: An anti-misinsertion structure of a socket connector includes a pivot clasped to both sides of the top of an insulating base of the socket connector and two connecting arms extended horizontally from both sides of the pivot. Each connecting arm has a guide piece extended horizontally from an end of each connecting arm, a stop piece formed at the bottom of the connecting arm and proximate to the guide piece of the connecting arm, a downwardly tilted first guide bevel formed at the bottom of the guide piece, a position limit surface defined on a side of the guide piece and proximate to the stop piece, an upwardly tilted second guide bevel formed at the bottom of the stop piece, and a stop surface defined on a side of the stop piece and proximate to the guide piece and perpendicular to the position limit surface of the guide piece.

column12: Safety needle assemblies and related methods
column13: The invention relates to a safety needle assembly and related methods. A safety needle assembly has a catheter cannula (152) attached to a catheter conduit (152) and a needle cannula (156) attached to a needle (158) protruding through the catheter conduit (152). A needle guard (122) is positioned in the interior cavity of the third cannula (164). The needle guard has a proximal wall (130) with an opening (132) and two arms (134, 136) each having an end (138, 140), and wherein in the ready position, the two ends are spaced from and biased toward the needle. The safety needle further has a support (126) located inside the cavity of the third cannula (164) and wherein, in the ready position, the two ends of the two arms on the needle guard rest on the support.
